[42.138, "o", "\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[0.013, "o", "\r\nNOTE: MariaDB is secure by default. Running this script is mostly\r\n      unecessary and it will likely be removed in a future release,\r\n      but it is for now preserved for backwards compatibility.\r\n\r\nEnter root user password or leave blank:\r\n\r\n"]
[0.010, "o", "Enter current password for root (enter for none): "]
[19.479, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.037, "o", "OK, successfully used password, moving on...\r\n\r\nSetting the root password or using the unix_socket ensures that nobody\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "can log into the MariaDB root user without the proper authorisation.\r\n\r\nYou already have your root account protected, so you can safely answer 'n'.\r\n\r\nSwitch to unix_socket authentication [Y/n] "]
[6.277, "o", "n"]
[2.595, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", " ... skipping.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "You already have your root account protected, so you can safely answer 'n'.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "Change the root password? [Y/n] "]
[7.936, "o", "Y"]
[2.458, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.007, "o", "New password: "]
[11.487, "o", "\r\nRe-enter new password: "]
[2.812, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.041, "o", "Password updated successfully!\r\nReloading privilege tables..\r\n"]
[0.041, "o", " ... Success!\r\n\r\n"]
[0.004, "o", "\r\nBy default, a MariaDB installation has an anonymous user, allowing anyone\r\nto log into MariaDB without having to have a user account created for\r\nthem.  This is intended only for testing, and to make the installation\r\ngo a bit smoother.  You should remove them before moving into a\r\nproduction environment.\r\n\r\nRemove anonymous users? [Y/n] "]
[12.953, "o", "Y"]
[1.933, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.033, "o", "Query OK, 2 rows affected\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "Normally, root should only be allowed to connect from 'localhost'.  This\r\nensures that someone cannot guess at the root password from the network.\r\n\r\nDisallow root login remotely? [Y/n] "]
[2.366, "o", "Y"]
[4.279, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.032, "o", "Query OK, 0 rows affected\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "By default, MariaDB comes with a database named 'test' that anyone can\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "access.  This is also intended only for testing, and should be removed\r\nbefore moving into a production environment.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "Remove test database and access to it? [Y/n] "]
[4.257, "o", "Y"]
[5.267, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", " - Dropping test database...\r\n"]
[0.039, "o", "Query OK, 0 rows affected\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n - Removing privileges on test database...\r\n"]
[0.029, "o", "Query OK, 2 rows affected\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "SQL executed without errors!\r\n\r\nReloading the privilege tables will ensure that all changes made so far\r\n"]
